---
title: One-Pan Moo Shu Pork Bowls with Cabbage, Scallions & Buttery Rice
description: This saucy, sweet, and spicy dish is ready in just 15 minutes—that’s faster than it takes to order delivery! Ground pork is browned with cabbage and scallions, then simmered in a blend of sweet Thai chili sauce, soy glaze, hoisin, and lime juice. It’s all spooned over buttery rice and garnished with sesame seeds for a nutty crunch.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pan-moo-shu-pork-bowls-b4c2b717.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pan-moo-shu-pork-bowls-61829f17c13a1e0a3e659b7b-b7646a6f.pdf
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: Asian
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 800 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 88 g
  sugar: 39 g
  protein: 29 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1460 mg
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-moo-shu-pork-bowls-61829f17c13a1e0a3e659b7b
---

Wash and dry produce.

Thinly slice @scallions{2%units}, separating whites from greens. Quarter @lime{1%unit}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
@ground pork{10%ounces} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned
and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Stir scallion whites and @shredded red cabbage{4%ounces} into pan with pork; cook
until just tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz}, 2 1/2 TBSP
@sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp} (5 TBSP for 4 servings), and @sugar{1/2%tsp}
(1 tsp for 4) until thoroughly combined. Turn off heat. Taste and season with
juice from half the lime (whole lime for 4), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, massage @microwavable rice{1%unit} in package to break up grains.
Partially open package and insert @butter{1%tbsp} (use 1 TBSP butter per package
for 4 servings). Microwave according to package instructions, ~{90%seconds}. Fluff
with a #fork{}.

> To make it easier to fluff the rice, transfer to a bowl first.

Divide rice between bowls and top with moo shu pork. Sprinkle with scallion
greens and as many @sesame seeds{1%tbsp} as you like. Serve with any remaining
lime wedges on the side.